commentText: It was fun watching your insta stories of your trip across Europe.  I just came back from Portugal and I loved it!  I tend to prefer spending several days in one place to really explore so I only visited Porto and Lisbon (with a day trip to Sintra).  My main purpose when traveling is always photography with food as the next most important thing.  Portugal is a great place for both of those things, especially the  food which is really cheap compared to what I'm used to paying back home in the US.  I did have some issues with the cobblestones as I'm not used to them and I find them a bit difficult to walk on especially when it rained (which it did a lot).  Lisbon and Porto are both very hilly and climbing up and down stairs, walking up and down steep streets was an everyday thing that you couldn't avoid.  Great thing about hilly cities though is so many viewpoints!  On my day trip to Sintra, my Apple Watch said I climbed the equivalent of 135 floors!  If you ever get a chance to visit, I would highly recommend it.  Portugal is definitely a place that many people are realizing is a great place to visit, however it still isn't as popular and as busy as cities like Paris or London for example.  If anyone is interested in my photos from my trip, I have some on my instagram: https://www.instagram.com/joits
